14 9.5–306.1.
15 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
16 INDICATED.
17 (2) “MARYLAND EXCELS” MEANS THE TIERED QUALITY RATING AND
18 IMPROVEMENT SYSTEM FOR EARLY CARE AND EDUCATION PROGRAMS
19 ESTABLISHED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
20 (3) “PUBLISHED” MEANS A MARYLAND EXCELS STATUS
21 INDICATING THAT THE EARLY CARE AND EDUCATION PROGRAM HAS:
22 (I) MET THE MARYLAND EXCELS REQUIREMENTS FOR A
23 SPECIFIED QUALITY RATING; AND
24 (II) A QUALITY RATING PUBLISHED ON THE MARYLAND
25 EXCELS PUBLIC PORTAL FOR PUBLIC VIEWING.
26 (4) “QUALITY RATING” MEANS A DETERMINATION, REPRESENTED BY
27 A NUMBER FROM 1 THROUGH 5, THAT A PARTICIPATING PROGRAM HAS MET THE
28 CRITERIA APPLICABLE TO A PARTICULAR SET OF MARYLAND EXCELS STANDARDS.
29 (B) IF THE DEPARTMENT DETERMINES THAT A FAMILY CHILD CARE
30 PROVIDER WITH A PUBLISHED MARYLAND EXCELS QUALITY RATING HAS
31 VIOLATED A REQUIREMENT OF THIS TITLE OR A RULE OR REGULATION ADOPTED

10 HOUSE BILL 1574
1 UNDER THIS TITLE, THE DEPARTMENT IMMEDIATELY SHALL NOTIFY THE FAMILY
2 CHILD CARE PROVIDER OF THE VIOLATION.
3 (C) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE FAMILY CHILD CARE PROVIDER SHALL
4 ENTER INTO AN AGREEMENT THAT DESCRIBES:
5 (1) THE NATURE OF THE VIOLATION;
6 (2) THE ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN BY THE FAMILY CHILD CARE
7 PROVIDER TO BECOME COMPLIANT; AND
8 (3) A PLAN FOR FOLLOW–UP BY THE DEPARTMENT TO ENSURE THAT
9 THE FAMILY CHILD CARE PROVIDER HAS RETURNED TO AND REMAINS FULLY
10 COMPLIANT WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS TITLE OR A RULE OR REGULATION
11 THAT WAS PREVIOUSLY VIOLATED.
12 (D) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
13 THE DEPARTMENT MAY REDUCE OR RESCIND A PUBLISHED MARYLAND EXCELS
14 QUALITY RATING IF THE FAMILY CHILD CARE PROVIDER:
15 (I) FAILS TO COMPLY WITH THE TERMS OF THE AGREEMENT OR
16 OTHERWISE FAILS TO CURE THE INITIAL VIOLATION; OR
17 (II) FAILS OR REFUSES TO ENTER INTO AN AGREEMENT.
18 (2) IF THE DEPARTMENT DETERMINES THAT THE VIOLATION DID NOT
19 INVOLVE AN IMMEDIATE RISK TO CHILD SAFETY AND THE FAMILY CHILD CARE
20 PROVIDER TIMELY RETURNED TO COMPLIANCE, THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT
21 REDUCE THE PUBLISHED MARYLAND EXCELS QUALITY RATING OF THE FAMILY
22 CHILD CARE PROVIDER.
23 (E) IF THE DEPARTMENT REDUCED THE PUBLISHED MARYLAND EXCELS
24 QUALITY RATING OF A FAMILY CHILD CARE PROVIDER, WITHIN 30 DAYS OF THE
25 PROVIDER RETURNING TO COMPLIANCE BY FULFILLING THE TERMS OF THE
26 AGREEMENT REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, THE
27 DEPARTMENT SHALL RESTORE THE PUBLISHED MARYLAND EXCELS QUALITY
28 RATING OF THE FAMILY CHILD CARE PROVIDER TO THE QUALITY RATING EARNED
29 BEFORE THE VIOLATION OCCURRED.
30 9.5–404.
31 (a) The State Board shall adopt rules and regulations for licensing and operating
32 child care centers.

HOUSE BILL 1574 11
1 (b) These rules and regulations shall:
2 (1) Ensure safe and sanitary conditions in child care centers;
3 (2) Ensure proper care, protection, and supervision of children in child care
4 centers, INCLUDING ESTABLISHING PROCEDURES TO BE FOLLOWED BY THE
5 DEPARTMENT IN RESPONSE TO A COMPLAINT ABOUT A CHILD CARE CENTER THAT:
6 (I) MAKE USE OF A UNIFORM COMPLAINT INTAKE PROCESS;
7 AND
8 (II) IMPLEMENT A STANDARDIZED COMPLAINT PRIORITY GUIDE
9 THAT DIFFERENTIATES COMPLAINTS BY THE SERIOUSNESS OF THE ISSUE RAISED,
10 INCLUDING DEFINED RESPONSE TIMES FOR EACH LEVEL OF COMPLAINT;
11 (3) Ensure the health of children in child care centers by:
12 (i) Monitoring children for signs and symptoms of child abuse;
13 (ii) Instructing licensees and staff concerning child abuse detection
14 and reporting;
15 (III) REQUIRING THE MAINTENANCE OF EMERGENCY
16 INFORMATION FROM A CHILD’S PARENT OR GUARDIAN THAT IS UPDATED AS NEEDED
17 AND REVIEWED BY THE PARENT OR GUARDIAN AT LEAST ONCE EACH YEAR;
18 [(iii)] (IV) Monitoring health practices to help prevent the spread of
19 disease;
20 [(iv)] (V) Monitoring the care of infants and children with special
21 needs; and
22 [(v)] (VI) Prohibiting the administration of corporal punishment to
23 discipline a child;
24 (4) Promote the sound growth and development of children in child care
25 centers;
26 (5) Promote proper nutrition and developmentally appropriate practices
27 by:
28 (i) Establishing training and policies promoting breast–feeding;
29 (ii) 1. Requiring compliance with the United States Department
30 of Agriculture Child and Adult Care Food Program standards for beverages served to

12 HOUSE BILL 1574
1 children, except that milk that is not nonfat or low fat may be ordered by a health care
2 practitioner or requested by a parent or guardian; and
3 2. Prohibiting beverages other than infant formula that
4 contain added sweetener or caffeine; and
5 (iii) Setting limits on screen time;
6 (6) Carry out otherwise the purposes and requirements of this subtitle,
7 including, WHEN NECESSARY, BY ENFORCEMENT THROUGH:
8 (I) THE imposition of intermediate sanctions to ensure compliance;
9 (II) ALTERATIONS IN THE MARYLAND EXCELS QUALITY
10 RATING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 9.5–411.1 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
11 (III) INDIVIDUALIZED PENALTIES IN ACCORDANCE WITH §
12 9.5–411.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE;
13 (7) Prohibit a child from remaining at a child care center for more than 14
14 hours in 1 day unless the Department issues an exception for that child based on guidelines
15 set by the State Superintendent;
