11 (c) (1) The probationary employment qualifications established under
12 subsection (b)(13) of this section shall allow an individual to be employed as a child care
13 teacher during a probationary period if the individual:
14 (i) 1. Is enrolled in approved pre–service training;
15 2. Successfully completes the required 90 hours of the
16 approved pre–service training within 6 months after being hired; and
17 3. Holds an associate degree or a bachelor’s degree in:
18 A. Early childhood education;
19 B. Elementary education;
20 C. Child development;
21 D. Home economics;
22 E. Nursing;
23 F. Social work;
24 G. Special education; or
25 H. A related field approved by the Department; or
26 (ii) 1. Is enrolled in approved pre–service training;
27 2. Has successfully completed at least 45 hours of the
28 approved pre–service training at the time the child care center hires the individual;

